Default Route (after login):
context.go('/home');

Switch to Tasker Flow:

On your settings screen, show a switch like:

SwitchListTile(
  title: Text('Become a Tasker'),
  value: isTasker,
  onChanged: (value) async {
    if (value) {
      // Prompt for skills, ID verification, etc.
      context.push('/tasker_setup');
    } else {
      // Maybe ask for confirmation before disabling
    }
  },
);


When they complete setup, update their profile:

await supabase.from('profiles').update({
  'is_tasker': true,
  'skills': selectedSkills,
  'bio': bio,
}).eq('id', userId);

üõ°Ô∏è Add Server-Side Checks (Optional)

You can restrict access to tasker-only features using Supabase Row Level Security (RLS) or Flutter-side checks:

-- Only allow verified taskers to bid on tasks
CREATE POLICY "Only verified taskers can bid"
ON bids FOR INSERT
USING (
  exists (
    SELECT 1 FROM profiles p
    WHERE p.id = auth.uid()
    AND p.is_tasker = true
    AND p.is_tasker_verified = true
  )
);

Feature	Recommendation
Roles	- All users are posters by default
Switching roles	- ‚ÄúBecome a Tasker‚Äù toggle in settings
Additional setup	- Collect skills, bio, verification
